github.lightningcreations.lcjei.resources

Interface ResourceKeyMapper<GuestKeyType,HostKeyType>

  • Type Parameters:
    GuestKeyType -
    HostKeyType - 

    public interface ResourceKeyMapper<GuestKeyType,HostKeyType>
    Represents a bi-directional function between the keys of a Host resource set and a Guest resource set.
    This interface defines a strict contract that mapToGuest(Object) and mapToHost(Object) must be inverse operations. That is, for any host key k, mapToHost(mapToGuest(k)) must be an identitiy operation.
    Additionally, the function must be a perfect function from the guest, that is the domain of the function MUST be the entire Guest keyspace.
    Author:
    chorm

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      GuestKeyType mapToGuest(HostKeyType hostKey)
      Returns the guest key that can be used with a MappedResourceSet to get the resource with hostKey.
      This method MUST be equality preserving and a perfect inverse to {mapToHost(Object).
      HostKeyType mapToHost(GuestKeyType guestKey)
      Returns the host key that backs the guest key in a MappedResourceSet.
      This method MUST be equality preserving and a perfect inverse to mapToGuest(Object).
      Failure to abide by this contract may have unexpected results.
      The mapping function does not permit null inputs and MUST NOT return null.

      • mapToGuest

        GuestKeyType mapToGuest(HostKeyType hostKey)
        Returns the guest key that can be used with a MappedResourceSet to get the resource with hostKey.
        This method MUST be equality preserving and a perfect inverse to {mapToHost(Object). Failure to abide by this contract may have unexpected results.
        The mapping function does not permit null inputs and MUST NOT return null.
        If hostKey is not in the range of the function, {mapToGuest(Object) returns null.
        Parameters:
        hostKey - the key used for the host ResourceSet.
        Throws:
        NullPointerExcept - if hostKey is null.
